sql:
SELECT report_id, report_date
FROM historical_reports
WHERE report_type = 'trend analysis';

external_knowledge:
- 'significant threshold' refers to AMSTEOE > 3000;
- 'trading activities' represent the trading volume for the day;
- 'busiest trading days' are determined by the highest trading volume.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.user_id, users.username, users.email
FROM users
JOIN access_logs ON users.user_id = access_logs.user_id;

SELECT 'AMSTEOE' AS index_name, m.date
FROM market_indices m
WHERE m.amsteoe > 275;

SELECT 
  (SELECT AVG(amsteoe) FROM market_indices) - 
  (SELECT AVG(failed_login_attempts) FROM users) AS final_result;

SELECT i.index_name, hr.report_type
FROM historical_reports hr
JOIN indices i ON hr.generated_by = i.index_id;

SELECT index_name, description 
FROM indices
ORDER BY index_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Significant user activity: At least 10 distinct active users; 
- Significant index involvement: At least 10 distinct market indices involved; 
- Average download duration: Average time users spent downloading content related to the report; 
- Average volume of indices: Average trading volume associated with the market indices involved in the report.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT index_name) 
FROM indices 
WHERE sector = 'Technology';
